parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, or loss of control, especially in wet weather conditions.
symptoms: The ABS warning light comes on
the brakes feel mushy or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the vehicle takes a long time to stop
the brakes lock up
or a pulsation or clicking sound is heard when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake pedal going to the floor can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or extended stopping distances.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels to the floor
the brakes feel soft or spongy
or the vehicle takes a long time to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake wear can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or extended stopping distances.
symptoms: The brake pads or rotors wear out prematurely
the brakes make a grinding or scraping noise
or the vehicle vibrates when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake manifold gasket can cause coolant leaks, engine overheating, and potentially lead to engine fires or damage, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Coolant leaks
engine overheating
loss of coolant
puddles of coolant under the vehicle
engine stalling
knocking noise from the engine
difficulty controlling the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause damage to the engine, lead to engine fires, or leave the driver stranded, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Engine overheating
coolant leaks
loss of coolant
puddles of coolant under the vehicle
engine stalling
knocking noise from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to not turn off completely, making it difficult to remove the keys from the ignition, which can lead to safety risks and potential theft.
symptoms: The vehicle will not turn off completely
the keys cannot be removed from the ignition
the ignition system is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, explosions, and other safety risks.
symptoms: Fuel leaking underneath the vehicle
fuel tank needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various components to malfunction, including the air conditioner, power windows, and engine, which can lead to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: Front driver and passenger side power windows fail to function
air conditioner fails to function
engine fails to start
brake lights and headlights fail to operate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the horn can cause a safety hazard, as the driver is unable to alert other drivers in emergency situations.
symptoms: Horn button is difficult to press
horn does not sound unless pressed very hard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine fires can cause significant damage to the vehicle and pose a safety risk to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Smoke and flames coming from under the hood.
